Mastering kubernetes with network troubleshooting tutorial

After starting kind cluster.

kubectl apply -f delay.yaml

then get into master node.

docker exec -it my-cluster-control-plane bash

#Install ping, telnet, ifconfig, bash, vim
#apt-cache search iputils-ping
apt update
apt-get install tcpdump
apt-get install curl

have 2 different master node terminals.

terminal 1. (replace host)

curl -i http://10.244.2.4/sleep/10

terminal 2. (replace host)

tcpdump -i eth0 host 10.244.2.4

to capture.

tcpdump -i eth0 host 10.244.2.4 -w capture.pcap

ship to windows.

docker cp <cotnainerid>:/capture.pcap .